Our #FMCWOWBox is surely spreading a lot of smiles and cheer, but our lovely partner Hey Deedee is the reason why in Mumbai. 😊
The delivery-ladies of Hey Deedee are personally delivering the Boxes to a lot of happy well-wishers across the city on their two-wheelers! ❤ Thank you for supporting us on our journey, and for making the journey for us too 😉

Hey Deedee is India's first all-women delivery service, founded by Revathi Roy. In a world where efficiency is key and time is essential, Hey Deedee provides an instant solution to your parcel delivery problems. Forgot an important document at home? Hey Deedee will fetch it for you. Need to send an urgent present for the anniversary you forgot? Hey Deedee will get it delivered. Simply book your order online, make your payment, and one of our specially trained female parcel delivery executives will get your parcels delivered safely and efficiently. The service can also be used for e-commerce and food businesses that require delivery agents.

FMC is proud to be associated with you ❤

Today I was very fortunate to partake in a huge milestone of this woman and I couldn't be more happier for her. I sometimes wonder how she does it by herself being a mother to a 6 yr. old, school, being in business for herself, and still push through all the other bs that comes along the way. By far one of the strongest, most courageous, dedicated, loyal, devoted mother, and friend all-in one! Today I say congratulations and my hat goes off to you for never giving up and being a positive role model for your daughter and others. Kudos to you for your hard work and never ending perseverance. Nothing makes me happier than to see this radiant smile of yours and to see you glow! I can't wait to see what's up next for you. Congratulations my friend and I hope to see you at your next milestone. #graduate #blessed #growth #levelup #mother #blackbeauty #entrepreneur #associates #bachelorsnext #proud #queen #goodteeth #biggestfan #niggawemadeit #beautyqueen

1. Love people while they're alive. 
2. Show appreciation while they can appreciate it. 
3. Don't wait until it's too late.
4. Treat people well. 
5. Stop all this hating.
6. Stop all this hypocrisy.
7. Stop judging.
8. Stop slandering. 
9. Cut this clique shit.
10. Accept your imperfections. 
11. Watch how you do people.
12. Give as much as you take. 
13. Know that you aren't God! 
14. Look at yourself in a mirror.
